706517f-a.title: Brooklyn: Rockaway Parkway - Smith's Lane
706517f-a.text:
1380-1384 Rockaway P'kway., at the S.W. corner of Smith's Lane. A
view of the Democratic Club of Canarsie in 1929; Subsecuently (1933) it
was occupied by the Holy Family Athletic Club. (Catholic).
July 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

706518f-a.text:
(1)
1400 Rockaway P'kway., west side, between Smith's Lane and Glenwood
Road, showing the Flatlands Volunteer Firemen's Association.
July 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, a different angle.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
